1 is considerably heavy than any normal sport shoe this could be due to the bulky sole that they have used to make the shoe durable it does look durable however i found that the sole is a bit jigglywobbly and not firm and stable which is needed for functionalcross training and even leg workouts the worst is when it comes to lateral movements when the shoe due to the unfirm sole feels very unstable and scary the sole just moves around itself like a jelly exaggerated which could make the user uncomfortable as one can tend to lose control
2 kept the shoe for casualwear as otherwise it is not working for me
3 the round toe box is very considerate and toes feel free in those regards but again this make the foot move around inside the shoes a bit more when it comes to lateral movements in this regard a narrow toebox secures the foot and doesn‚Äôt allow any internal play i have noticed this flaw in my other zerodrop shoes xero

unfortunately i will move back to my metcons and decathlons i love to support homegrown brands but this didn‚Äôt work out for me better than expected just superb feel is good for is good grip is amazing surely recommend all to buy at least one pair the basic problem with these is that they are not well cushioned from the sides especially near the foot joint the insole is also not glued to the inner side of the sole which causes it to fold and sometimes slip inside the shoes resulting in less traction if the foot is not comfortable inside the shoe  also slips because of the problem with insole the walk is not pleasant i hope the company improves it comfort look and nice styling very nice products very comfortable and looks very nice
